Singer, Beyonce, has announced that she will be going on a global tour, the first in seven years. This comes weeks after she performed her first show in years in Dubai. The singer announced the tour on her Instagram page on Wednesday, with a picture of herself atop a stationary shiny horse. ALSO READ: Details of all EPL completed January transfer deadline day deals She captioned the photo, “RENAISSANCE WORLD TOUR 2023.” Fans have been expressing excitement at the news in her comment section. While, actress, Ini Edo, commented, “Okuuur” with the fire emoji, Nigerian singer, Yemi Alade said, “Let’s gooo,” with double fire emojis. Beyonce’s last tour was in 2016, the Formation tour, which was in support of her sixth album, Lemonade. 